{"questionId":"70b33953-aa61-407d-a25a-a438792bed03_3","correctAnswer":"A","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Factor the second equation","content":"Rewrite: $\\dfrac{cx}{4y}=\\dfrac{c}{4}\\cdot\\dfrac{x}{y}=52$."},{"title":"Combine and compute","content":"Substitute $\\dfrac{x}{y}=52$: $\\dfrac{c}{4}\\cdot 52=52$, so $\\dfrac{c}{4}=1$ and $c=4$.<br/><br/>The answer is <strong>A</strong>."}]}